document_data.mainbody:
'''Icewind Dale''' was an arctic tundra located in the [[Frozenfar]] region of [[the North]], It earned its name from the harsh winds and icy storms that destroyed buildings and scoured the landscape.
{{Quote|If I could choose what life would be mine, it would be this life that I now have, at this time. I am at peace, and yet, the world around me swirls with turmoil...The reality of existence here in Icewind Dale is harsh indeed, an environment unforgiving, where one mistake will cost you your life.|[[Drizzt Do'Urden]].}}

{{TOC limit|3}}

Geographical Features.Mountains:
[[File:IWD HoW WMap.jpg|thumb|right|300px|''A view of Kelvin's Cairn, Lonelywood, and Maer Dualdon.'']]
* [[Kelvin's Cairn]], a peak that offered fresh water to the surrounding lakes when "spring" bloomed every [[Midsummer]].
* [[Mount Shatterglass]], the {{SIAdj|3000|ft|adj=tall}} peak that offered a spectacular view over the dale below.{{Cite adventurers league/Cold Benevolence|9}}

Notable Locations.Landmarks:
* [[Black Cabin]], a solitary lodge that served as a refuge for many who traveled across the dale.{{Template:Cite book/Icewind Dale: Rime of the Frostmaiden|116}}
* [[Damien's Tower]], the cursed residence of [[Damien Morienus]].
* [[Dorn's Deep]], a dwarven fortress located on a lone peak in the Spine of the World.
* [[Jarlmoot]], the ancient meeting place of the region's frost giants.{{Template:Cite book/Icewind Dale: Rime of the Frostmaiden|137}}
* [[Lost Spire of Netheril]], a mage tower that was torn asunder from the [[Netherese enclave|enclave]] of [[Ythryn]].{{Template:Cite book/Icewind Dale: Rime of the Frostmaiden|145}}
